6 WHEREAS, Louisiana's franchised dealers demonstrated their commitment to their
7 communities by contributing more than twenty million dollars to charitable organizations
8 during the previous year; and
9 WHEREAS, since 1937, the Louisiana Automobile Dealers Association has united
10 automobile dealers across the state, advocated for their interests, promoted ethical business
11 practices, and supported policies that foster economic growth and the long-term vitality of
12 Louisiana's automotive marketplace.
13 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
14 does hereby commend the next generation of new car and heavy truck dealers of the
15 Louisiana Automobile Dealers Association for their leadership, service, and contributions
16 to the state of Louisiana, does hereby recognize the unwavering commitment of Louisiana
17 Automobile Dealers Association members to excellence in service, does hereby extend
18 enduring appreciation for all that these individuals do for Louisiana, and does hereby
19 designate Tuesday, April 14, 2026, as Louisiana Automobile Dealer Day at the Louisiana
20 State Capitol.
